Every major corporation started as a small business in someone’s garage or dorm room. These success stories are because of the opportunity that exists in the United States of America. 

Someone can take a good idea, apply a little elbow grease, and create a business.

In recent decades, the government has encroached further and further into small businesses’ operations, levying unfair taxes and burdensome regulations.

Thankfully, President Donald Trump’s tax cuts helped level the playing field for small businesses.
